We consider your desire for dissolution whether it be agreement or litigation and provide advice tailored to your specific circumstances. Regardless of your location in Spain we are able to assist you in your divorce through existing local partnerships and expert relationships with divorce lawyers throughout Spain and the rest of Europe.

What do I need to know about divorce in Spain?

Separation

If you can amicably separate without the need for a court file it can take approximately one month.

Common law relationships

The principle courts which deal with cases involving common law relationships are known as “Ocasion Autos” (occasionally initiated civil actions) and these can range from a couple of months to one year, depending on the particular circumstances. This is not straight forward, but we can get you advice easily and would encourage common law relationship couples to seek specific advice on their relationship and finances.

Paternity testing

Not an issue in Spain, unlike in other countries where there is no official way to determine the paternity of children in common law relationship – at least not legally. This can become difficult and expensive for a father who loves his child and wants to be a part of their lives.

Child residence and custody (GuardiaI y custodia) / Aliamento parents

Guardiai and custodia usually go together although it is possible to have one without the other.
